title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text:
The food is pretty good.  Not great, but good.  We did the Wurst platter, some perigees and spaetzel.   All good, with a special nod to the kielbasa which was fantastic.

The place is well worn, and the marina isn't ever going to be confused for Monte Carlo.

The staff were friendly.

The biggest thing....it's on the water....which is really nice.  If the place were in Maine or Mass it would be "rustic".  BYOB...OK food and a nice setting....it's worth a visit.  The place has Octoberfest written all over it.  Cool weather on the deck with a few beers and a brat or two....I'll be back.

title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text:
This is one of my favorite places in New Haven. I’m an NYC expat always searching for places that remind me of my homeland. The food here is homemade, tasty and authentic. I’ve seen the reviews where people complain about the service,  and how only 1 person waits all the tables. Totally understandable if you’re in a major rush. It seems that the restaurant is family owned and operated which, to me, is a big plus. If you’re looking for fast food, this is the wrong place. If you’re looking for great food, home style vibes, great culture and a meal that will nourish your soul, come here.
By the way, don’t embarrass yourself by asking for a fork. Live a little and use your hands.

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text:
1 star for a subpar/gross experience at Chicago Getaway Hostel. I rented a private room for 3 nights looking for a clean/decent place to sleep and shower while I was in the city for a work project. Chicago Getaway Hostel did not fit the bill.

The Hostel is in a beautiful Lincoln Park neighborhood with tons of giant trees and you really can't find a better location to get the LP vibe but then walk a block to hop on trains/buses. The cost for a private room is comparable to a hotel room, but I chose this place because it's location was within walking distance to where I was going to be working. After looking at reviews and photos of the hostel, it seemed like a very modern and clean place that I would be comfortable staying at... unfortunately the photos were deceiving and the reviews did not represent my experience.

When I walked up to the building, I had to walk through a crowd of people gathering on the sidewalk outside the hostel smoking (great for my asthma) to enter the building. This happened every time I entered/exited the building over the next few days, which was a real turn off to me. The check in process was quick - the person checking me in rushed through all of the instructions and gave me no written document that verified what he went over, so that was fun.

My room looked nice at first glance - 2 bunk beds, a desk, shower/toilet/sink. All the essentials. Upon further investigation here's what I found (some photos attached)... the bathroom was absolutely disgusting. I don't know when it was last cleaned, but it had to have been a long time. The amount of dirt/grime built up in that shower made me feel dirtier than I was when I walked in. One shouldn't have to buy flip flops to shower in a private room bathroom they rented. There was buildup ON THE SHOWER HEAD where the clean water is supposed to come out of but there was nastiness caked on so it passed through that first.

The beds were pretty uncomfortable. The mattress was very thin and I could feel the bars through it, so it was rough sleeping. A majority of the linens had a ton of stains/loose hairs on them (especially the pillows) and they were very rough in texture. All of this combined made me feel very gross and like the room hadn't been cleaned at all. For the price of a hotel room I'd expect a much higher level of cleanliness from this place.

Needless to say, I will not be back.
name: Ash C

The omelette was done perfectly with just the right amount of cheese and veggies. The salad was really fresh and the baguette was just toasted enough to be tasty without making the bread dry. title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text:
I stayed in this hostel for almost two months just off-and-on. The hostel is quite large and one can often find as much, if not more, peace and quiet there than in an apartment. The majority of the kitchen's storage and dishes are at Taylor Apartment next door, but the café-style drink area and good deal of outdoor seating can be beneficial.

The venue is known primarily as a place for partying and many do or have at some point but that doesn't have to ruin it for the rest of us. There are a good number of quite friendly and helpful staff who lessen the severity of mistake which could get you a "boot" (permanent removal). It is a hostel after all. I once left my laptop three weeks and returned to find it safe and sound by the staff behind the desk. The place is clean overall and even after many years bit of wear and tear can be seen; but the wifi was always very fast and reliable

text: I went here the day after they opened up and the museum is beautiful. Their space is so nicely set up, lit, organized and has a gorgeous gift shop. If you like ceramics, art and pretty things I highly recommend this trip. ___ I partially went to this to paint but it ended up being a fun trip to go on alone. I had a great experience here, the art studio is cute and inviting. There's a coat and bag check which is nice and helpful. The barista at the cafe is great, the studios are happy, the gift shop is wonderful and I pretty much just had a great time. The prices for our time are 15 for a adult for a single and 25 for a couple. Totally worth it. You'll have a great time. They accept most credit cards too.

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text:
I am disgusted. As I just sit in this bed because I don’t want me feet all over who knows how many guests before me. We stopped here so we didn’t have to continue to drive on our long trip. All we wanted was a clean hotel where we could sleep and shower with our two children! The shower even has black hairs! Black hairs were all over the first room and we asked to switch to find the same thing. The floors are not vacuumed at all. It’s unreal. I have never stayed at a Wyndham hotel but it looked VERY nice in the photos and I never imagined it would be this dirty. The cleaning in this hotel... well there obviously wasn’t any real cleaning done. There should never be leftovers from other strangers in a hotel I paid for. I would have rather drove three more hours then not have a nice place to sleep and shower at. I am very upset and I have NEVER in my life wrote a review. I am not hard to please! The Wi-Fi code does not work. The phone does not work. The phone plug keeps falling out every time I pick up the phone. The top layer of the sheet had dirt on it or food. Looks like cake. I stay at many hotel. This is unacceptable. Also On top of this. I was told you guys price match. There was a deal online that was $20 cheaper than the right here and they said they could not do it. So even more annoyed right now that I came here because I thought I was getting a deal. After having heart issues with my bank it took a little longer than necessary which is totally my fault. My car got blocked because were out of town. I would have paid the extra money to stay in a clean hotel but after carrying all of her bags and everything up for four people, me and my husband have to work tomorrow. title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text:
I visited Chicago for a Pearl Jam concert & stayed here for 3 nights. I loved the experience. This was my first stay in a Hostel, & I was nervous at first, but that quickly changed when I sat in the common area & chatted with people from all over the world. Everyone was so friendly, & I met several PJ fans.
The price was very affordable & they had everything I needed + some. If you don't mind sharing a room, this is a great place to stay.
The hotel staff was very friendly & helpful, & let you store your bags if you arrive before check-in.
I shared a room with 6 other females (8 bed room). Bunk beds come with sheets, 1 pillow, 1 thick blanket, 1 locker, & 1 towel. You will need to bring a lock for the locker, or you can purchase one for $5.40 at the front desk. There is an ac window unit & a portable heater in each room.
Women's bathroom had 3 stalls & 3 showers with a hair dryer & several shared shower products that are removed on Mondays.
There are about half a dozen computers, a printer (free), lots of space to sit & lounge, pool & Foosball table, 2 televisions with plenty of seats, & a very nice patio area with bicycle rentals.
There is also a big kitchen you can use any time, huge eating area, 3 refrigerators, 1 freezer, bins & labels to store your food, plenty of shelves to store dry food, ice machine, vending machines, & Kuerig with coffee & hot chocolate. There is an onsite laundry room with laundry soap & fabric softener available for purchase as well.
I hope this helps!! Safe travels!!
name: Angela S

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: Very clean, great location - just what we needed.

title: Quality Inn & Suites

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text:
It was really nice. There were a lot of negative reviews for no good reason. The room was clean, the carpet was clean, and the ventilation was VERY impressive. We had no issues with noise from next door.
They accommodated our over-night stay after initially denying it. My partners boss had passed away during a conference and it was a traumatic experience for all involved.
I'm not one to complain about "little things" in a hotel. For example, the selection local TV channels was poor. However the remote was finicky.
Trash cans in public spaces were not always emptied. Legitimate complaint but it's not like they intentionally did that. 
And someone was smoking in the casino which was annoying but they put up enough signs to warn people.
I'll stay here again, probably in the casino though.
name: Dennis Willis

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text:
Minutes after we walked into our room, I started having severe dust allergies, and the place was filthy. I was shocked because we expect so much more from a Marriott. I called and asked for the room to be cleaned while we were gone for a few hours, telling them that the floor was really dirty and the phone had so much dust on it it appeared it hadn't been cleaned in a very long time (just to give them some examples of the problems.) When we came back, it was clear someone had wiped down the phone briefly and swept the tile floor in the doorway, but the room was still filthy. I called again and let them know, and to their credit, they upgraded us to a much nicer much cleaner room. And I wasn't allergic to this room which was visibly less dusty and dirty.
We were thankful for the upgrade, but it should have never been necessary. I shouldn't walk into a room in a Marriott property to find it so dirty.

I have attached pictures of the floor in the bathroom, the floor in the entryway, the phone, and the shower curtain, which had grime and very questionable hairs crusted onto it...
name: Kassi L

title: Ray’s Splash Planet

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text:
Pros: some fun stuff for kids! Go karts, bumper boats, rock climb, trampoline jump. There are also laser tag and mini golf available. There is a game room with some arcade style games, snacks, etc. Kids will love everything here, and you might too.

Cons: EXPENSIVE! Understand before you go that tickets for just outside activities are $30 per person... For 2 hours. That's $120 for a family of 4. Want to play a doubt of mini golf? That's not included... That's another $18... Per person. So now you're up to $200. Wanna try laser tag?it's very fun, but also not included.

Your kids will want to play the arcade games to win tickets, you can buy game passes for a time limit.

During fully open operation and during the summer it is *crowded* so lines are long so be prepared to wait.

Bottom line - kids will have a blast, go on off-peak days if you can, look online or ask about packages for activities and games, and be prepared to shell out a lot of money for the afternoon; if you're not ready to either drop a couple hundred bucks or disappoint the kids by telling them "no" then maybe come back a different time.

title: Trap Music Museum
text:
Have you ever been confronted with history? Walking through the gates of the Arlington National Cemetery Amphitheater, sometimes it is a heart attack that hits you... man... this is real...

Or maybe not.

Since the moment I walked directly into the first conserved WWI exhibition, on the walls was this tapestry of a bomber pilot writing in his diary. A black and white drawing, consisting of one character in the drawing. The flight stick has moon and star on it. The driver looks out of the plane and finds a moon. Go figure, nobody knows what kind of plane this is, but in my imagination it is a German monoplane. It is a bi-plane with a striped roundel on the tail of the planes. Can this be a familiar aircraft registration to the Imperial Air Force that flew over the trenches in support of the kaiser’s ground assault to victory? We can guess. This German pilot writes in his diary, the star it

title: Round 1
text:
1/2022:  RECOMMEND, but 3.5 stars if possible due to 2 details:

If possible, go during the WEEKDAY for Unlimited bowl until 5pm for $11.99. I've hurt my arms & shoulders from bowling way too many games during this inexpensive time and improved my bowling scores.  (Thank you Round 1).

I've enjoyed going to Round 1 to relax and enjoy the oversized Pac-man game and bowl some stress away.  I have not tried the food nor drinks there because I just go in to play games.

Mostly clean, spacious and social distancing  protocols are  in effect.  Team members were constantly cleaning.  My only negative comment is that no one has cleaned the escalator entrance and it looks unwelcoming/unsightly.

Overall, give Round 1 a try and see what you think about it.  Enjoy the games!

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text:
This place is great! It’s got a wide variety of games. When you first walk in, it looks like any arcades you visited growing up. After you check out the current selection, you start to get a feeling for their vast selection. The coin mechanism for most games gives you two credits for a quarter. If you have got a few dollars you can kill a lot of time stumbling through their games. If you see something you like, but aren’t up for that game, they have got a few stations they are donating the original cartridges to folks coming in to try things out. I highly recommend coming down here with some friends after work.
Recently they did a live stream while they played Qbert. It was pretty fun to watch. Most weekends they have some sort of a tournament or event. Check out their webpage for more info on upcoming events. I feel pretty excited to go try some of their other games!

text: So incredibly disappointed.. I use to love the Hilton Daytona oceanfront property but this stay was definitely disappointing. After arriving in the room I went to use the restroom and noticed the bathroom hadn’t been cleaned. During these times with many uncertainties this was very concerning. I searched our room after noticing the bathroom wasn’t clean and found a bug shell on our bed! We called the front and the quickly moved us to a different room . No bug shells on this bed but the room was still very sad and the pictures on the wall even had broken glass in the frame. I talked so highly of this property and after this stay I am embarrassed of how highly I spoke of it . title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text:
I enjoyed the docent taking me around the museum. And I’m glad he didn’t take time for the sun dial to tell me it’s no longer an accurate representation, which would have caused the museum to lose out on all sorts of unproductive time researching when, if, for how long, etc sun dials, moon dials, water clocks and sundials etc have been used to tell time. Instead he told me the history and functionality without saying that it no longer is an accurate representation (because of course history repeats !!) leaving me to remember that sometimes it’s more pleasing (and magical) to total immerse in the experience rather than question your sanity and see the numbers like in the digital world.
There’s nothing he could have done to improve. It was all just perfect. Thank you to him and the library.
name: Molly Porter

text: We arrived about 2hrs before twilight to the hotel bar and bought the twilight package that included 2 drink tickets, 2 cups of popcorn, a t-shirt and book, and general admission to watch twilight from the field (another $35 per person on tickets) and had no problems watching the movie from the field. The package cost was $89. The theater itself is small and is really really hot but its a historic theater in the area. Its cool if you want to see the movie in an historic theater. The package deal is worth it if you want to watch it with the limited view. Pack your sunscreen!! This is Washington state. 🙂

title: The Westin Hilton Head Island Resort & Spa
text: What an awesome experience we had over Independence Day weekend! The pool is fantastic, with plenty of room for kids and adults to play, not too deep, a spacious jacuzzi nearby, and plenty of lounge chairs (although here's a tip: claim your chairs by 8am on busy weekends!). We enjoyed the games and activities for the 4th of July, and the BBQ buffet (with s'mores) was delicious! The private beach access is a huge bonus as well. We look forward to returning for another family getaway!
name: Chris Schweighart

title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood
text:
Went here for my husband's birthday! Everyone here was very kind and made sure to celebrate him. The food was absolutely delicious, spritz' were great, what can I say? This is one of the best upscale restaurants in Town Center Plaza.

I have to make a separate paragraph for the dessert. Nikki did a fantastic job. It's a peanut butter custard with brownie cubes and buttered pecans. One of the best desserts I've eaten!
name: Veronica Kindersmith

title: Electric Playhouse
text: Great spot to take your children everyday or to friends parties or just make it a date night 😍
name: Roy Edwards

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: Would recommend for younger kids, maybe elementary school aged. Took my teen there, and although she did have fun because she loves marine animals in general, this place is geared more for the younger ones. And look for “less than busier” times if you like to read everything. There is lots of great information all over. Have fun!
name: Pauline Torres

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text: Saw Ready Player One today. Was EPIC, loved every second!
name: Maureen Lee

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text:
It is a bit tight inside and the service was just ok, but the food was excellent. My wife had enchiladas, I got the seafood fajitas and we both had the meal with a house salad and house rice and beans.
It took an almost hour to get our meal, so I was worried she wasn't going to get hers before she had to leave. Which would have been unfortunate since the fire alarm was going off and nobody at the restaurant seemed to care.
The fajitas were pretty big, hers were with 3 chicken and 3 shrimp. Mine was plump mussels and scallops, some of the mussels were a bit rubbery, but otherwise good. The satay sauce was good for the chicken, but I think it would have been better with a different ranchero sauce for the seafood fajitas and I had to go out of the way to get some container and hot sauce from the other table since nobody seemed to care.
name: Russell Heath

title: Bowlero Cherry Creek
text: Anadarko and Junior Achievement
name: Jana Husch

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Great food, great service
name: Christopher a Stickler

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text: It was a great place to stay, very clean. Staff were very nice.
name: Pamela Ward

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text: This place has everything good service clean rooms pool room divider 👍👍👍... two fingers up for these hotel
name: Bethan May

title: The LINE LA
text: First the good, friendly staff, breakfast was great and the rooms were very clean and was nice and quiet. But this hotel taken over by the new owners in November of 2018. They said that the hotel has been closed for clean up and restoration for 2 months. It looks like this is not the case at all! Revealing that deceiving photos makes me think that I should no longer trust any of the photos or reviews on here. So this review is NOT about the hotel itself but about how deceptive the entire Yelp site is!
name: Joseph Webb

title: Trap Music Museum
text: I enjoyed it! The details are dead on! Staff were personable, parking wasn't as bad as I anticipated lol and the design and layout of everything was just dope!!!

title: Hungry Howie's Pizza
text: Pizza was delicious.
name: Ben Lee

title: Saltgrass Steak House
text:
This is a fantastic little hidden gem near Rt 6 surrounded by trees and off the beaten path. It's easy to miss as there is no clear signage just one sign in front of the building you are looking for.
More of an order at the counter type establishment seating only 30. There was an older couple ahead of us that were taking their good old time quite awhile.


They don't accept plastic, so make sure to bring cash. They have several items cooked over the open fire from a list of daily specials and sandwiches.
We ordered the filet with a loaded baked potato for $27.00. They come with soup or salad which is first come first served  since if you have to overly staffed.
We were brought sliced hot peppers in olive oil to snack on while we waited.
The salad was great, I stayed with the low fat ranch house dressing and the fresh salad greens were fresh tasting...not wilted like other restaurants.
Just a great value
name: Lynn Lynch

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text:
The staff is friendly. It's easily accessible and easy to get to downtown, only took ~20 minutes.
The outside and interior is in good condition.

My non-smoking room was on the third floor, was in good condition and didn't smell. However, the elevator and the entire 3rd floor smelled like cigarette smoke. The closet was tiny, but there were plenty of drawers in the dresser.

The room had plenty of room to walk around in and for a couple of people to sit comfortably. I had a king size bed and it was very comfortable.

Breakfast was alright. I had sausage patties, scrambled eggs, biscuits and gravy and a waffle with coffee and oj. Coffee tasted like flavored water. They also had apple juice, toast, bagels, cereal and oatmeal.

All together, I enjoyed my stay. If I'm ever back in the area, I will consider staying here again.
name: Eric Bonar

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Very tasty food and great service!
name: Terence Roberts

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text: nice rooms,  helpful staff,  free bkfst next door at the restaurant!!!
name: Con Brennan

title: Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort & Spa
text:
We had mixed feelings about our stay at this Hilton.  First off, the pictures of the family suites are deceiving.   We thought their would be an extra room with a king or two doubles.  Their was not.  It's all one big room.  When you walk in their are bunk beds, (the ceiling was low and the ladder was steep) then a hallway, bathroom ( with no lock on it, by the way) then the bed with a table & sofa ( that turns into a bed) then balcony.   They do have multiple restaurants, but  all of them were pricey.  They did give us a free ice cream, it was pretty good.  Alex who checked us in was very helpful.

They have multiple pools, but if you dont get  out to the lounge chairs by seven your out of luck!  Beachfront was great!  You have to rent chairs & umbrellas for the beach, so we just brought our own.  The hot tub in the indoor pool jets did not work.

Overall we enjoyed our stay.
We ate a lot off property since we had a lot of activites planned.
We really enjoyed the beachfront access & the views.
name: KL Dice

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Huge indoor paintball arena with so many cool games. They have you fill out waiver electronically before going there but rules were not enforced and I saw a lot steel shots made. Apparently there was one minor incident that led to owner being somewhat restrictive/overbearing but overall good arena
name: Amelia Gray

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: This place is awesome! The free birthday party was fun hosting it and the kids had fun playing!
name: Sandra Collins

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: This was such a pleasant surprise for my companion and I; it has been on my list for years! Well worth the wait. Beautiful renovation of the building, lovely setting. We wanted to love our meals, but much of the food had some element that was not my preferred presentation however it was very tasty. I had the scallops and risotto to start; scallops were cooked perfectly but the risotto was a bit cold, not quite right at room temperature. The cheescake I ordered was probably the best I've had with highly recommend that dessert. Our dining companions thought the pork chop and gnocchi with mushrooms were great. Overall, the service and ambiance made this a special restaurant which this town needs more of, cheers!
name: Paul Edwards

title: Honeycomb Bed & Breakfast
text: Beautiful property, rooms in the "bungalow" are very nice with one 1 queen and two twins in a bedroom with a full kitchen. Bathroom is attached to bedroom, with a tub and shower. Outhouse is located directly across from building. Fire pit is located across from buildings in field. Lot’s of windows to look out and see the beautiful landscape. Breakfast in a basket is served on a dark, green tray: Biscuits, sausage, fruit, and a muffin. Very good food, however, I wish the couple would use some other type of plate other than the tray for serving their dish. The plate causes the nicer looking tupperware to get messed up through the week. I would consider staying here again.
name: Vanessa Dunn

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: just an incredible museum. worth the visit.
name: Russell Raymer

title: Marine Motel
text: Stayed at the Country Inn and Suites in Meridian, Idaho.  The room was quite large, the bathroom was quite spacious and well outfitted.  The hotel is geared with a restaurant and Starbucks store.  There is a nice business center with computers.  A conference room which I was told can be used for showers.  There is a small upright piano in the center of the floor.  I wish I had brought some CDs to leave for others to enjoy.  The restaurant however is quite expensive but the food was very good.  The bed was quite comfortable and the package was quite reasonably priced.
name: Mitchell Rose

title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text: The platter was quite delicious & filling that I ended up having leftovers to go. This spot is worth visiting & I look fwd to the day when the live music will be back though that which was playing still helped to warm up the socially-distanced setup.
name: Laura Saint Jean

title: Honeycomb Bed & Breakfast
text: It was an absolutely beautiful stay and the breakfasts were amazing. The service was also amazing and super friendly. Would definitely come back for another stay.

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: It seems like it has improved from 6 years ago... sea dragon exhibit was awesome, the whole family loved it!

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text: A pretty nice hotel.  Jamie at the front desk greeted and helped us with our stay. The pool was great, kids enjoyed themselves and we had a good time.  Rooms were clean and appeared to be recently updated.

title: Hotel Bel-Air
text: Concord have been to it once before and I have to say that it is rich in history. It is now fixed with a Great staff and terrific dining experience especially in the lounge area. Warm with clean and rich in atmosphere.

title: Ray’s Splash Planet

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text: Quick trip to Kansas City. Hotels aren’t as cheap as they used to be. Staff was helpful, the room opened up to the outdoor pool and the breakfast was okay.. pancakes, cereal and juices. The rooms were small a bit tight with 2 kids that’s why I enjoyed being open to the pool

title: Wendy's
text: Great place with friendly staff and fresh hot coffee. The best in Branford.

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text: Too many people, there were some very rude people here. When we went most of the slides were not working and some of the best slides were broken so they should fix that while they're closed. The water was more clear than it has been previous years but there was still leaves in the water. The biggest disappointment was that the lazy river was closed off after only 5 minutes of being in the river.
name: Mathew Foster

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text:
Clean, convenient, very friendly 🏳️‍🌈. Not many food options and a little overpriced for the area, but felt safe. ToGo Breakfast Bags and Coffee/Tea/Vending in Lobby. Also has a small Route 66 gift shop and a Chevron right next door.

Very nice, best looking single night option before AZ from CA. Smoking areas available outside the rooms. No elevator... two levels, external doors. Adhered to COVID-19 restrictions, masks required and worn.

Great sunrise over the pool. 🌅

title: The LINE LA
text: Great hotel, parking is an issue if you're driving here.

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text: A place to eat sushi if you have no choice! Location on foot you can see traffic light, so employees are not worried about speeding. 10 pieces of vegetable gyoza (tofu) in the menu is 8 pieces! They will choose from the tray all those who’s on the edge, but good digestion!

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text:
Always a fun time and easy to spend almost an hour here even in the middle of winter weather.
Visited for the first time, had grandkids with us, wished we had visited years ago.
It was great having them run free, no burdens or concerns just having fun.
Visiting this place in the warmer seasons would definitely focus on the coaster side though.
We will definitely be making several returns in the coming months.
Thanks Frontier.

title: Crowne Plaza Shenandoah - Woodlands Area, an IHG Hotel
text: We had a group of 3 families from Chicago here and we had a great time at the hotel and in the Woodlands area as a whole. The staff at the hotel were fantastic, professional and helpful.We celebrated my daughter's 22nd  birthday and the Chef prepared a special dessert we all could share and chocolate covered strawberries for the Birthday girl!  The rooms were like brand new,  the lobby was sharp, modern and impeccably clean. The pool was beautifully designed with comfortable outdoor furniture. This hotel is highly recommended.
name: Mary Biancalana

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: This is a must if you come to Portland. Just like a mini Seattle. They have a cool history. The restaurant is a bit of a walk but well worth it. Of course we enjoyed this dinner! Blown away just by the amazing smell and atmosphere. Great service and we enjoyed our dinner 😋

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text: Great place to take your kids!!! Small price BIG FUN!
name: Just Smith

title: Denver Zoo
text: The zoo is amazing! The animals are kept very well and everyone seems to love them which translates to having a very happy healthy animal. There are many animals from birds and reptiles, to mammals, fish and of course the big cats! There are picnic areas to eat in most locations. There is live entertainment and several train stations you can ride around the park and the train guide is great at explaining the history of the animals and the park. My three yo really enjoyed the zoo. The train was a little much for him and in our opinion this zoo would be considered more of park and maybe if he was older would hold his attention more. But other than that we had a great time and would recommend as an evening vist
name: Jacob Byrne

title: Quest Motel
text: Clean. Small TV. Old microwave that could not be run at same time as the coffee maker or you'd trip the breaker.

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Please bring your own snowshoes or rent, a lot of trails are closed but there are 4 open trails, you can rent sleds at 1/2 mile south of the park on the west side of the road.
name: Georgia Barlow

title: The LINE LA
text:
I love boutique hotels. And The Line LA is now on the top of my list. The design is super fun, while being both thoughtful and playful. 5 stars for the service, the staff here is friendly and engaged. I’m on the 8th floor in a King room with an expansive view of the Hollywood hills. My room has the bed, a desk and additional seating which I really enjoy using. I like how spacious my room is. I don’t want to get out of bed, it’s cozy and comfy, not stiff. The bath did not disappoint, soft towels and a dojo type robe that I appreciated for its light weight.
I had dinner and wine at the hotel, and again, great service. The food had a fresh take that was interesting and delicious. I’m in town for the weekend and The Line is a perfect fit.

This is an update. I returned to The Line for three days during Christmas. Same great service. My family joined me for Christmas Day brunch at the newly opened Openaire restaurant. The meal featured rolling carts with sides that were inventive, tasty and fun.
name: Deborah Kuchar

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text: It was an amazing experience. I won a free room for 8 people through my theatre program at Grandview High School. My theatre teacher knows the owner and she held a competition for people to win it. I came out in first and loved every time I have reached out to Breakout. They have always been so considerate of my situation when ever I have questions.
name: Elijah Enchalada

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: our second time here... same great experience... hospitality and welcome is warm, friendly and exceptional!! right off the interstate, pet friendly, clean and updated. we will be back again...
name: Leah Norris

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text:
Has to be the absolute worst hotel I have ever stayed at.  First room at check in had bed that was half slept in, couple pillows were missing covers, sink had been used with open soap and wet towel sitting on counter.  Front desk gave a different room... AC didn’t work, nasty stains on furniture, sink area was nasty/not cleaned... toilet wouldn’t flush so called fr my desk.  ‘Engineer fixed it’ while we were gone for the day but no, actually didn’t fix.  Doesn’t flush.  Gross place.  Highly recommend not staying here.  Old, tired, worn out property.
Even the bathroom linens were gross & old.
As you can see in the photos, staff DO NOT clean at all.  I’d say this bathroom hasn’t been cleaned a few months.
name: Jason Wood

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text:
This place is "Starting" to grow on me. Much better atmosphere than my visit back in November 2021. Masks are encouraged but not Forced on you. The Food court has gotten back into it's groove and the options are plentiful and given a 4 Day 3 night stay we had tried just about everything with no complaints. The main Restaurant was superb, my Steak couldn't have been cooked any better and exactly as I requested. Medium with no seasoning only salt and hint of cracked pepper. This place still has plenty of real table games(it's nice have a real human for a dealer). They still have a mix of virtual table machines but the balance was much better than a lot of other out of the way casino resorts are going. Great selection of slots but still like all the other casinos, they are very tight. The areas for those not able to gamble was open and they had plenty to do to keep them busy. I recommend you check out their website to see all the options and entrainment available to anyone traveling with young people. I seen quite a few on this trip and they seemed quite happy and talkative. In all, we enjoyed this visit but I still miss my Wisconsin favorites. However, this one will definitely grow on you. Enjoy and definitely Good Luck! You'll need it, Lol.
Update 8-14-22; I just spent two nights here and this place just keeps getting better. Slots seem to be a little less tight and I actually walked out ahead this time, significantly 😁. I noticed a lot more staff, slot attendants doing hand pays, Security, cleaning personal and the drink servers we're around checking up on everyone very regularly. I still have to get used to the higher drink prices ("We're not in Wisconsin anymore"😂). The area is Beautiful and lots to do if you need a break and you're not in the gambling mood. If only they had a Spa this would definitely be a 5 ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Resort. Hint, hint!!!
name: Kenton Wiedenbeck

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Was here for a hiking trip. The staff in the store was very friendly. Got a nice little map of all the places around the area to hike. Stores food and cook supplies, little or anything you might need. There's a hiking guide in the room to help you get a good hike in.
name: Francesca Jones

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text: Great place to watch a movie, drink a soda and watch the previews. The theater is nice and clean. Its box theater, so you see pretty much everything on the screen.

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text: I stayed here the weekend of the Notre Dame homecoming. loved it.  besides the half hour wait to check in the place was great.  big ass trundle bed.

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Staff was very friendly, and gave great tips on how to play. Would come back!

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text: Amazing bang for your buck. Only US place with many conveyor belt options

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: This hotel was very clean and comfortable. I enjoyed the bar and the Starbucks located in the lobby was very convenient in the morning. I did not like the fact that they don’t have room service, and there aren’t any restaurants or anything walking distance to the hotel.
name: Marquila Ferrell

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: Enjoyable pulling my boat up, sitting on the deck. Food was great also. BYOB.

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: Great service, very friendly and helpful. Food was ok and over priced.
name: Victoria Lewis

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text: Great park for the family. Loved the caves, a little dark but totally worth it. The zip line was a hit between my kids and myself. The only thing missing is a bigger wave pool but not big enough to comeback over it. Still it’s a fun, clean, family park. UPDATE: I received an amicable response to my re charge my complaints above.  Perhaps the ride operators were overtaxed  or some other poor management. That said, I was so impressed and happy to charge re point out that my positive experience last night and the on point response i received makes them a five star park and I regret having kicked it down to a three star. Thanks, See you soon and bring a towel!
name: Katie Patel

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: broken showers! like the air conditioning, the place totally deteriorated

title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text: Best ever and one of the first places I eat at when I return to the states and is home

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text:
Cute place to stay. There is a small swimming pool and gym, but not only open, depends on the season.
Not far from the airport. Any questions better ask by call at Customer service.
There are nice greens around the hotel. That's why there is amazing smell of flowers and greens 🌺🌺🌺 outside 👍

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: Probably the best IMAX in the country.  Planetarium is marginal, but the whole package is terrific.  Especially for kids.  Another great thing about this place is that it's open during the hours when many other cultural spots are closed.  It's a surprise every time.  Definitely worth checking out.  Highly recommended.
name: Jacob Warren

title: Addis Restaurant
text: It was my first time. This place is absolutely amazing. They are very friendly and the food is amazing. I bought 4 specials to go. I had never seen a place with this variety. Their deserts looked just as amazing as the savory dishes. I wish we had a place here like this.
name: Rachael Wall

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: Dog-friendly, reasonably priced, and well maintained!  Ice cream and candy selection is even cute.  Can’t say enough good things, still a kid at heart, even in my 30s.
name: Michelle Wilson

title: Frankie's of Charlotte
text: It was so much fun!!! I was a bit apprehensive with the Sky Coaster.. I'm a wimp on things like that with my weight and I was nervous.. but it was super easy (literally) it was a blast! Staff was incredible and helpful! If I can give a 6 star tip it would be totally warranted in this case- I will definitely be back to see everybody again! Thank You!!!!
name: Melissa Matthews

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text:
The checkin experience was truly amazing! First of all the lobby is gorgeous, when I checked in there was a group of two employees in the back, they were singing and getting their spirits high. When I called  be to do the checkin, after a couple of minutes the attendant came out, turned right back around and went to the back again to pick up his co-worker to help me check in. It wasn't the fact that they were singing but the communication and attention to detail that was displayed by these employees! Thank you! My room, magnolia was great and spacious! The air con was on, it wasn't necessarily loud but you do hear it all the time. All of these small things don't affect my stay, but these small things do make my stay so much more pleasant.

I will refer all my friends and family to stay at the Hilton Fort Lauderdale.

I'm looking forward to my next visit.
name: Kenneth Clarke

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: Great amenities. They market room service to order off the menu, but since it is a fancy hotel everything costs $30 and up. Gone are the days of $10 cheeseburgers. It wasn't available on the menu, but I was able to get a chicken caesar salad. It was good but way overpriced. There is no coffee pot. Not a deal breaker, but annoying. The fitness center has every machine you could want, but the bike seat is covered in shampoo crumbles and hair product. Hopefully the cleaning crew is putting these products where they are supposed to be! It is a 10+ minute walk to the convention center if you use the tram. Take the tram and get off right outside. If it's sunny the walk is brutal in the heat.
name: Eileen Lawrence

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: I live in the area and stayed there after cutting off my finger. I experienced the excellence and attention to detail from the moment I walked in to the moment I walked out. Star of the show was Summer in registration. Tina in the pharmacy was great making sure everything went smoothly. Vanessa in house-keeping was great! Joe and Craig I think defended my gushing as W and when you’re a nurse in recovery from a disaster ( I guess the finger bite was just that), you need the support. Best service. Love that we have this quality of hospitals locally.
name: Dominic Thomas

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text: I never understand why people bitch about cheap people eating and drinking inside the theatre. The whole reason they have a concession stand is to sell popcorn and other snacks like candy, sandwiches, candy, etc. If you have to go to the bathroom go at the beginning of the movie and try to go fast and make it in under 10 minutes but hopefully the movie isn't as good as this movie.
name: Toby Harding

title: Hungry Howie's Pizza
text: Ordered 3 Chicken Bacon Ranch Subs and a Small Double Peppperoni Pizza for my family and I tonight. The 3 subs were delivered at 5:25 PM CST and the delivery girl told me she forgot the small double pepperoni pizza. Tell me why it's 6:37 PM CST and the pizza was just now delivered. Google says we are only 2.5 miles away. So why does my pizza take an hour to an hour to arrive after all my other food? So called double pepperoni pizza looks like single as every slice literally looks like they ensured manually it has no more than 4 pepperoni slices each. Absolutely ridiculous!
name: Nelson Mejia

title: First Western Inn Caseyville
text:
I like this place better than the Motel 6 and Quality Inn.

They have RV parking... :)
name: Joe Bender

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: Everything was great! The service, the food, everything. I had the eggplant and it was so wonderfully stuffed with ricotta and a tomato sauce. The only thing is you have to go there sober because the fun begins once you are drunk (at least for me).
name: Marcus Shaw

title: Home grown GA Restaurant
text: Great food, great place and good service.
name: Hannah Hopkins

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: $7.50 for kids and $9.50 for adults. Lots of fun and challenging holes on the Mini Haunts course. The other course was closed for painting when we were there. Lots of golfers out practicing on the driving range as well! Late afternoon was a good time to come.
name: Erin Miller

title: The Westin Hilton Head Island Resort & Spa
text: Hospitality was average.  Nothing breathtaking or bad.  Went to the summit on their snow wolves ride and it was fun.
name: Sally Lawrence

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Really fun field. Had a blast. The folks behind the desk were really great and it seems like they really know how to keep the place fun for regular and occasional players.
name: Adrian Williams

title: Sky Zone Trampoline Park
text: Staff was rude not helpful at all. Staff stood around in a circle whole time playing with each other. Ignored me when needed assistance.  Really hot & musty in here. No a.c. really filthy. Water fountain dosent work.Basketball courts were closed If I could give it 0stars I would. Never coming back here again and really DONT recommend it at all!
name: Zuleima

title: Holiday Inn Express & Suites Swift Current, an IHG Hotel
text: We liked the location and cleanliness of this hotel. We booked through Expedia to get the 5th night free, but it is not affiliated with La Quinta. You need to call the condo company they are renting the condo out to at 757-616-5500, I believe. This is the number the representative gave us and the number on the paperwork given to us at check in by the gentleman. Be aware the 1st 2 days you won't be able to park in the guest parking lot, you will parking on the main street. Haul your luggage as far as you can, but you need to make sure you have a room, first. If you don't like this area, there isn't much else around. Pool is on the small side. It is a nice pool, just small. Some rooms are closer to the pool floor than others. The HVAC in the condo works good and cools down the whole condo good. It is a nice safe
name: Tracy Wood
